data.title: Campus briefs
data.text:
Utah

TENNIS: The University of Utah men's tennis squad is on the road this week to compete in the Rolex ITA Region VII Championships in Las Vegas. The tournament will be the host to nearly 100 collegiate tennis players and will be held at UNLV's Fertitta Tennis Complex. Competition will begin Wednesday, Oct. 25, and continue through Sunday. The winners of both the singles and doubles competitions will advance to the 2001 Rolex National Indoor Intercollegiate Championships in January.

BYU

SWIMMING:The BYU men's and women's swimming and diving teams will host in-state rival Utah in the first dual meet of the season, Friday at 6 p.m., in the Richards Building Pool. Both the men's and women's teams are set to defend their Mountain West Conference Championships.

Southern Utah

BASEBALL: Southern Utah coach Kurt Palmer announced the signing of former Dixie High and Dixie College first baseman Dan Wright Tuesday afternoon. Wright has transferred to SUU from the University of Nebraska, where he played last season.

SUU opens the 2001 season with a three-game series at national-power Arizona State Feb. 2-4, in Tempe, Ariz.

CROSS COUNTRY: SUU's men's and women's cross country teams travel to Macomb, Ill., this Saturday for the Mid-Continent Conference Championships, hosted by Western Illinois. The women's 5-kilometer race will begin at 10:15 a.m. (CDT), while the men's 8K run will follow at 11:00 a.m. (CDT), at Spring Lake Park.

The Thunderbird men enter Saturday's championship as the three-time defending conference champions, having won every title since joining the Mid-Con in 1997, while the women's team has won the past two Mid-Con titles after taking second in their debut race in 1997.
